

{#        INTRO PARA FOR DATAPANINO: DEFINE WHO, WHAT AND WHY#}
{#        <p>#}
{##}
{#          DataPanino is a visualization tool that shows intellectual property (IP) sales and applications in 7 #}
{#          European Union countries from 1965 to 2015. It's intended to help users identify insights and trends, #}
{#          showing IP sales against a backdrop of economic indicators. Users may include analysts, investors, #}
{#          companies, and governments. Anyone can sign up.#}
{#
{##}
{
{#        </p>#}
{#        <h5> Why only 7 EU member countries?</h5>#}
{#         <p>#}
{#        France, Germany, Italy, Netherlands, Spain, Switzerland, and the United Kingdom are given priority because they#}
{#        show the highest amount of patent applications and the highest ICT patent applications to the EOP by priority#}
{#        year (REVISE!) from 2004 to 2015. As defined by "Eurostat," intellectual property rights (IPR) inlcude the#}
{#        "assignment of property rights through patents, refers to the general term for the assignment of property#}
{#        rights through patents, copyrights and trademarks. These property rights allow the holder to exercise a#}
{#        monopoly on the use of the item for a set period."#}
{#        <a href="http://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/statistics-explained/index.php/Glossary:Intellectual_property_right">#}
{#            Eurostat</a> </br>#}
{#        <a href="http://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/statistics-explained/index.php?title=Intellectual_property_rights_statistics&stable=0#Context">#}
{#        Eurostat</a>#}
